  "issue_title": "Inconsistent exit codes and JSON aggregate semantics vs human tables",
  "issue_body": "\n## Description\n\n1. **`gitt issues list --id`:** For an on-chain ID that does not exist, `--json` exited with code `1` and emitted a structured error payload. Human mode printed a yellow warning and exited `0` for the same outcome.\n\n2. **`gitt miner check --json-output`:** The JSON field `invalid` was computed as `len(results) - valid_count - no_response_count`, which counted validators with `has_pat is False` (\u201cno PAT\u201d in the table) together with invalid PAT rows.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `gitt issues list --id 999999` (use an ID not on chain for your contract) without `--json`; note exit code.\n2. Same with `--json`; note exit code.\n3. Run `gitt miner check --json-output` on a netuid where some validators have no PAT; compare per-row labels to the top-level `invalid` number.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nSame exit code for the same logical error across human and JSON modes; JSON aggregate fields should match the categories shown in the human table (or the table labels should match JSON).\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nHuman list exits `0` for missing `--id`; JSON list exits `1`. JSON invalid mixes \u201cno PAT\u201d with truly invalid PAT responses.\n\n## Additional context\n\n### Issues list (`gittensor/cli/issue_commands/view.py`)\n\n- When `--id` is set and the issue is not in the contract read result, human mode now uses `print_error(...)` and `raise SystemExit(1)`, aligned with JSON\u2019s non-zero exit and the same \u201cnot found on-chain\u201d wording family as JSON.\n\n### Miner check (`gittensor/cli/miner_commands/check.py`)\n\n- Added `_pat_check_aggregate_counts(results)` so JSON totals follow the same branches as the human table: **valid**, **no_pat**, **invalid_pat**, **no_response**.\n- JSON payload now includes `no_pat` and `invalid_pat` instead of the ambiguous top-level `invalid` key.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Gittensor CLI, Python 3.x, any OS\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-26T03:02:59.000Z",
